NAME: People Serving People
NOTES: Families with children under the age of 18. Guests are screened and referred by Hennepin County.  accepts ex-offenders reentering general population from a correctional facility.

NAME: Simpson Emergency Shelter
NOTES: The overnight shelter is for 44 men and 22 women, 28 day stay (with potential expansion to 90 days) for single sober adult men and women; limited number of nightly stay beds.

NAME: St. Anne's Place
NOTES: Emergency shelter for women-led families who are homeless

NAME: St. Stephen's Emergency Shelter
NOTES: Nightly shelter to 45 sober, adult men

NAME: Salvation Army - Harbor Light
NOTES: Emergency shelter for single men and women

NAME: Our Savior's Shelter
NOTES: 28 day stay (with potential expansion to 90 days) for single ans sober adult men and women.

NAME: Avenues for Homeless Youth
NOTES: Homeless youth ages 16 to 21 from the northwestern suburbs of the Twin Cities

NAME: Families Moving Forward
NOTES: No night-time shelter at site. Daytime shelter and will process clients to local congregations.

NAME: Hope Street Shelter
NOTES: For 16 - 20-year-olds. Families are contacted if possible.

NAME: Exodus Residence - Catholic Charities
NOTES: Priority is given to homeless individuals from Hennepin Health and North Memorial, those who are 55-years-old or older and those experiencing acute/chronic medical issues.

NAME: The Bridge for Youth Minneapolis
NOTES: Overnight stay only, For 10 - 17-year-olds who may be reunified with family, For 16 - 18-year-olds who are unable to be reunified with family

NAME: St. Joseph's Home for Children
NOTES: Emergency shelter placement and basic needs for children from birth to 17-years-old,needs referral

NAME: Catholic Charities Higher Ground
NOTES: Emergency homeless shelter and Pay-for-Stay facility.  Hours 4pm-9am.

NAME: House of Charity
NOTES: Individuals wishing to enter House of Charity of Housing must be referred by a case manager, outreach worker, or other professional.

NAME: First Covenant Church Salvation Army
NOTES: Shelter for 50 men and women. Open from November to April, 6PM-7AM

NAME: Evergreen Residence
NOTES: Shelter with 88 units of single room occupancy, permanent housing for independent, single adults, recreational activities, with access to Narcotics Anonymous meetings.

NAME: Glenwood Residence
NOTES: Shelter with 80 units of permanent housing to late-stage, chronic alcoholics, health care screenings, case management with structured goal planning and three meals.
